{"parse":{"title":"Death by a Thousand Cuts (book)","pageid":25919213,"revid":753808372,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Death by a Thousand Cuts <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Death+by+a+Thousand+Cuts&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BTimothy+Brook%5D%5D%2C%3Cbr+%2F%3EJ%C3%A9r%C3%B4me+Bourgon%2C%3Cbr+%2F%3EGregory+Blue&amp;rft.date=15+March+2008&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BHarvard+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=336+pp.\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Death by a Thousand Cuts.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/ca/Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"226\" data-file-width=\"150\" data-file-height=\"226\" /></a><div>Front cover of <i>Death by a Thousand Cuts</i></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Timothy_Brook\" title=\"Timothy Brook\">Timothy Brook</a>,<br />J\u00e9r\u00f4me Bourgon,<br />Gregory Blue</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nHistory</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University_Press\" title=\"Harvard University Press\">Harvard University Press</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n15 March 2008</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (<a href=\"/wiki/Hardcover\" title=\"Hardcover\">Hardback</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n336 pp.</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-674-02773-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-674-02773-6\">0-674-02773-6</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Death by a Thousand Cuts</b></i> is a book by the historians <a href=\"/wiki/Timothy_Brook\" title=\"Timothy Brook\">Timothy Brook</a> and Gregory Blue and scientific <a href=\"/wiki/Research\" title=\"Research\">researcher</a> J\u00e9r\u00f4me Bourgon which examines the use of <a href=\"/wiki/Slow_slicing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slow slicing\">slow slicing</a> or <i>lingchi</i>, a form of <a href=\"/wiki/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">torture</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Capital_punishment\" title=\"Capital punishment\">capital punishment</a> practised in <a href=\"/wiki/Mid-Imperial_China\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mid-Imperial China\">mid</a>- and <a href=\"/wiki/Late_Imperial_China\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Late Imperial China\">late-Imperial</a> China from the tenth century until its abolition in 1905.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HarvardBlurb-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Awards\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#About_the_authors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">About the authors</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Other_reviews\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Other reviews</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Synopsis\">Synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Synopsis\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox mbox-small-left ambox-content\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"[icon]\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/30px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"31\" /></a></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section <b>needs expansion</b>. <small>You can help by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=\">adding to it</a>.</small>  <small><i>(January 2010)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i>Death by a Thousand Cuts</i> investigates the use of <a href=\"/wiki/Slow_slicing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slow slicing\">slow slicing</a> or <i>lingchi</i>, a form of torture and capital punishment practised in mid- and late-Imperial China from the tenth century until its abolition in 1905.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HarvardBlurb-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <i>Lingchi</i> involved repeatedly slicing the <a href=\"/wiki/Convict\" title=\"Convict\">convict</a>'s flesh beyond the point of death.<sup id=\"cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TimesHigherEducation-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NewYorker_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NewYorker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>By the time of the final imperial dynasty, the punishment could be meted out for an offence as simple as striking a teacher.<sup id=\"cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TimesHigherEducation-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The authors argue that this was more than a physical punishment, as the victim was <a href=\"/wiki/Sedative\" title=\"Sedative\">sedated</a> with <a href=\"/wiki/Opium\" title=\"Opium\">opium</a> and killed early in the process, but about denying the victim \"somatic integrity\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NewYorker_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NewYorker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-SomaticIntegrity_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SomaticIntegrity-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and denying them any hope of a <a href=\"/wiki/Afterlife\" title=\"Afterlife\">life after death</a> which, the authors argue, caused them to feel <a href=\"/wiki/Shame\" title=\"Shame\">shame</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NewYorker_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NewYorker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A staff reviewer at <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_Yorker\" title=\"The New Yorker\">The New Yorker</a></i> describes the book as a \"fascinating study\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-NewYorker_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NewYorker-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A staff reviewer at <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Times\" title=\"The Times\">The Times</a></i> states that \"the authors present a nuanced picture of state-imposed execution and, without at any time condoning, succeed in their goal of contextualising <i>lingchi</i> in relation to Western forms of punishment\" and that \"this challenging and important work will appeal not solely to <a href=\"/wiki/Sinology\" title=\"Sinology\">Sinologists</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sinology_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sinology-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> but to <a href=\"/wiki/Legal_history\" title=\"Legal history\">legal historians</a> and students of visual representation.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-TimesHigherEducation-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jonathan Mirsky in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Literary_Review\" title=\"Literary Review\">Literary Review</a></i> writes that \"[the authors] write coolly and formally, but this is a book primarily about torment.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-LiteraryReview_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-LiteraryReview-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards\">Awards</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Awards\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>Death by a Thousand Cuts</i> was a finalist and received an honourable mention for the Professional/Scholarly Publishing (PSP) Division of the <a href=\"/wiki/Association_of_American_Publishers\" title=\"Association of American Publishers\">Association of American Publishers</a> 2008 PROSE Award, in the World History and Biography/Autobiography category.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HarvardBlurb-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ProseAward2008_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ProseAward2008-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"About_the_authors\">About the authors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: About the authors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Timothy_Brook_(historian)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Timothy Brook (historian)\">Timothy Brook</a> is Professor of History at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_British_Columbia\" title=\"University of British Columbia\">University of British Columbia</a>. J\u00e9r\u00f4me Bourgon is a researcher at the Institut d\u2019Asie Orientale / <a href=\"/wiki/French_National_Centre_for_Scientific_Research\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"French National Centre for Scientific Research\">Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Lyon\" title=\"Lyon\">Lyon</a>. Gregory Blue is Associate Professor of History at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Victoria\" title=\"University of Victoria\">University of Victoria</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HarvardUniversityPress_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HarvardUniversityPress-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Death_by_a_Thousand_Cuts_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 35em; -webkit-column-width: 35em; column-width: 35em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-HarvardBlurb-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-HarvardBlurb_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Staff (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.hup.harvard.edu/catalog.php?isbn=9780674027732\">\"Death by a Thousand Cuts: Timothy Brook, J\u00e9r\u00f4me Bourgon and Gregory Blue\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University_Press\" title=\"Harvard University Press\">Harvard University Press</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-01-28</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Death+by+a+Thousand+Cuts%3A+Timothy+Brook%2C+J%C3%A9r%C3%B4me+Bourgon+and+Gregory+Blue&amp;rft.pub=Harvard+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.au=Staff&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hup.harvard.edu%2Fcatalog.php%3Fisbn%3D9780674027732&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADeath+by+a+Thousand+Cuts+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-TimesHigherEducation-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-TimesHigherEducation_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Staff (8 May 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?storyCode=401789&amp;sectioncode=26\">\"Death by a Thousand Cuts\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Times\" title=\"The Times\">The Times</a> Higher Education</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-01-23</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Times+Higher+Education&amp;rft.atitle=Death+by+a+Thousand+Cuts&amp;rft.date=2008-05-08&amp;rft.au=Staff&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeshighereducation.co.uk%2Fstory.asp%3FstoryCode%3D401789%26sectioncode%3D26&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADeath+by+a+Thousand+Cuts+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-NewYorker-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-NewYorker_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NewYorker_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NewYorker_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-NewYorker_3-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Staff (5 May 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newyorker.com/arts/reviews/brieflynoted/2008/05/05/080505crbn_brieflynoted4\">\"Death by a Thousand Cuts\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_Yorker\" title=\"The New Yorker\">The New Yorker</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-01-23</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+Yorker&amp;rft.atitle=Death+by+a+Thousand+Cuts&amp;rft.date=2008-05-05&amp;rft.au=Staff&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Farts%2Freviews%2Fbrieflynoted%2F2008%2F05%2F05%2F080505crbn_brieflynoted4&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADeath+by+a+Thousand+Cuts+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SomaticIntegrity-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-SomaticIntegrity_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Somatic integrity: the vital capacity to be whole as an organism, which would be denied if the body were cut into pieces.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Sinology-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Sinology_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Sinology: the study of China  and things related to China.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-LiteraryReview-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-LiteraryReview_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Mirsky, Jonathan (November 2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110723173956/http://www.literaryreview.co.uk/mirsky_11_08.html\">\"Slice and Dice\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Literary_Review\" title=\"Literary Review\">Literary Review</a></i>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.literaryreview.co.uk/mirsky_11_08.html\">the original</a> on 2011-07-23<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-01-23</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Literary+Review&amp;rft.atitle=Slice+and+Dice&amp;rft.date=2008-11&amp;rft.aulast=Mirsky&amp;rft.aufirst=Jonathan&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.literaryreview.co.uk%2Fmirsky_11_08.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADeath+by+a+Thousand+Cuts+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span><